  -- For each j ‚Č† k, let E_j be the first call where k learns j's secret,
  -- and L_j be the last call where j learns k's secret.
  -- Each call not containing k can cover at most one of these 2(n-1) events,
  -- whereas each call containing k can cover at most two (E_j and L_j).
